          <title>Early Humans Used Complex Tools Made from Animal Bones 1.5 Million Years Ago</title>
          <description><![CDATA[A new study reveals that early humans in Tanzania's Olduvai Gorge site used complex tools made from animal bones around 1.5 million years ago, pushing back the date for ancient bone tool use by about a million years.]]></description>
